00:05:32.680 --> 00:05:35.230
who refuse to admit
that biology matters.

00:05:35.230 --> 00:05:38.784
Some of the key canards
that you typically hear,

00:05:38.784 --> 00:05:41.200
some of the key objections--
there are many more of these.

00:05:41.200 --> 00:05:44.530
I discuss this-- by the way,
the book that Jordan kindly

00:05:44.530 --> 00:05:47.480
got for you guys, "The
Consuming Instinct,"

00:05:47.480 --> 00:05:49.780
I discussed many of
these detractors,

00:05:49.780 --> 00:05:52.030
but let me just mention
a few very briefly.

00:05:52.030 --> 00:05:54.550
So here's one typical
argument you hear.

00:05:54.550 --> 00:05:57.400
Well, biology is
great to explain

00:05:57.400 --> 00:06:00.130
the behavior of the mosquito
and the zebra and the dog,

00:06:00.130 --> 00:06:02.410
but surely, you
can't use biology

00:06:02.410 --> 00:06:04.330
to explain human behavior.

00:06:04.330 --> 00:06:07.120
This is called the
human reticence effect.

00:06:07.120 --> 00:06:08.830
The exact same
evolutionary principle

00:06:08.830 --> 00:06:12.250
might apply to every possible
species except humans.

00:06:12.250 --> 00:06:14.200
Evolution stops right here.

00:06:14.200 --> 00:06:19.270
Somehow our brains come
through a magical process

00:06:19.270 --> 00:06:21.550
that's outside of
evolution, which,

00:06:21.550 --> 00:06:24.230
of course, is ridiculous.

00:06:24.230 --> 00:06:28.950
Here's a second
one you often hear.

00:06:28.950 --> 00:06:31.410
Evolutionary
psychology is dangerous

00:06:31.410 --> 00:06:35.220
because it quote "justifies"
and condones reprehensible

00:06:35.220 --> 00:06:35.880
behavior."

00:06:35.880 --> 00:06:40.110
So for example, if you explain
why child abuse might happen

00:06:40.110 --> 00:06:44.520
or why rape happens or why men
and women cheat on one another

00:06:44.520 --> 00:06:46.530
in an otherwise
monogamous union,

00:06:46.530 --> 00:06:49.110
then somebody will come
along in a very irate manner

00:06:49.110 --> 00:06:52.924
and say you're using science
to condone and justify

00:06:52.924 --> 00:06:53.590
these behaviors.

00:06:53.590 --> 00:06:55.140
Of course you're not doing that.

00:06:55.140 --> 00:06:57.720
The oncologist who
studies pancreatic cancer

00:06:57.720 --> 00:06:59.850
is not for cancer.

00:06:59.850 --> 00:07:02.440
He's not justifying cancer.

00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:06.220
He's studying honestly cancer.

00:07:06.220 --> 00:07:10.260
And so if you study
child abuse and rape

00:07:10.260 --> 00:07:12.210
and marital infidelity,
that doesn't

00:07:12.210 --> 00:07:13.210
mean that you're for it.

00:07:13.210 --> 00:07:15.168
That doesn't mean that
you're trying to come up

00:07:15.168 --> 00:07:16.710
with an umbrella to justify it.

00:07:16.710 --> 00:07:19.251
It means that you're trying to
honestly understand these very

00:07:19.251 --> 00:07:21.070
reprehensible behaviors.

00:07:21.070 --> 00:07:23.250
Here's another one
that comes up often.

00:07:23.250 --> 00:07:26.430
This is what I call
the but men are not

00:07:26.430 --> 00:07:28.300
taller than women because Tom--

00:07:28.300 --> 00:07:29.430
not Tom Jones.

00:07:29.430 --> 00:07:30.880
What's his name?

00:07:30.880 --> 00:07:32.430
What's the actors name?

00:07:32.430 --> 00:07:33.630
Tom Cruise.

00:07:33.630 --> 00:07:34.590
Tom Jones.

00:07:34.590 --> 00:07:35.490
I'm showing my age.

00:07:35.490 --> 00:07:40.650
Tom Jones was a was a
sex symbol in the '70s.

00:07:40.650 --> 00:07:43.410
So Tom Cruise is shorter
than Katie Homes who

00:07:43.410 --> 00:07:46.380
was his ex-wife, therefore aha!

00:07:46.380 --> 00:07:49.820
it's not true that men
are taller than women.

00:07:49.820 --> 00:07:55.500
The cognitive bias there is
that people take a single datum

00:07:55.500 --> 00:07:58.650
to falsify a statement that
holds true at the population

00:07:58.650 --> 00:07:59.320
level.

00:07:59.320 --> 00:08:01.350
So if you explain,
on average, men

00:08:01.350 --> 00:08:04.080
prefer to mate with
nubile, fertile women

00:08:04.080 --> 00:08:05.624
more so than
post-menopausal women,

00:08:05.624 --> 00:08:07.290
someone will put up
their hands and say,

00:08:07.290 --> 00:08:09.870
but that's not true because
my Uncle Joe is dating

00:08:09.870 --> 00:08:11.450
an older woman named Glenda.

00:08:11.450 --> 00:08:12.690
Oh gee, Darwin is dead.

00:08:12.690 --> 00:08:14.790
We're back to the
drawing boards.

00:08:14.790 --> 00:08:16.350
Of course that's not true.

00:08:16.350 --> 00:08:19.000
But again, that's the cognitive
vice that people succumb to.

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:22.020
And this is the one that
irritates me the most

00:08:22.020 --> 00:08:24.810
because it is the
one that typically

00:08:24.810 --> 00:08:28.320
is levied by otherwise
sophisticated academics.

00:08:28.320 --> 00:08:30.360
They say that evolutionary
psychology is just

00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:33.870
a bunch of fanciful
post-hoc stories

00:08:33.870 --> 00:08:35.980
that you come up
with after the fact.

00:08:35.980 --> 00:08:37.730
Nothing could be
further from the truth

00:08:37.730 --> 00:08:40.139
as I will show you
in a few slides.

00:08:45.310 --> 00:08:47.410
This is going to be a
bit the technical part

00:08:47.410 --> 00:08:48.485
of the presentation.

00:08:48.485 --> 00:08:50.110
And then later, I'll
give you some sort

00:08:50.110 --> 00:08:54.080
of sexy, practical examples.

00:08:54.080 --> 00:08:56.620
So the epistemology of
evolutionary psychology,

00:08:56.620 --> 00:08:58.880
or for short, I'll
just call it EP.

00:08:58.880 --> 00:09:03.190
So the method of EP is really
comprised of three components.

00:09:03.190 --> 00:09:05.650
When you're doing
evolutionary research,

00:09:05.650 --> 00:09:08.645
you really are doing
these three things.

00:09:08.645 --> 00:09:10.020
You first have to
differentiate--

00:09:10.020 --> 00:09:12.167
and I'll explain each
of these in turn.

00:09:12.167 --> 00:09:13.750
You have to differentiate
between what

00:09:13.750 --> 00:09:15.760
are called proximate
and ultimate scientific

00:09:15.760 --> 00:09:17.200
explanations.

00:09:17.200 --> 00:09:20.360
That's a fundamentally
important distinction.

00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:21.970
And I'll talk about
this in a second.

00:09:21.970 --> 00:09:24.190
You build what are called
nomological networks

00:09:24.190 --> 00:09:26.959
of cumulative evidence,
very, very important.

00:09:26.959 --> 00:09:28.000
Again, I'll explain this.

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:29.625
And then you also
build what are called

00:09:29.625 --> 00:09:31.270
consilient trees of knowledge.

00:09:31.270 --> 00:09:34.840
Consilience basically
means unity of knowledge.

00:09:34.840 --> 00:09:37.900
Physics is more
consilient than sociology,

00:09:37.900 --> 00:09:40.450
not because physicists are
smarter than sociologists,

00:09:40.450 --> 00:09:43.450
but because physics has
organized its knowledge

00:09:43.450 --> 00:09:47.110
base in a way where there are
these organized, coherent trees

00:09:47.110 --> 00:09:47.830
of knowledge.

00:09:47.830 --> 00:09:49.480
Sociology hasn't.

00:09:49.480 --> 00:09:52.210
We can't agree in
sociology whether there

00:09:52.210 --> 00:09:55.030
is such a thing as innate
sex differences or not.

00:09:55.030 --> 00:09:56.010
OK?

00:09:56.010 --> 00:10:00.382
So I'll explain each
of these in turn.

00:10:00.382 --> 00:10:01.840
So let's begin with
this first one.

00:10:01.840 --> 00:10:07.110
So here I'm going
to discuss this one.

00:10:07.110 --> 00:10:11.480
The difference between proximate
and ultimate explanations.

00:10:11.480 --> 00:10:15.170
Much of science operates
at the proximate level.

00:10:15.170 --> 00:10:17.570
Most Nobel Prizes that
have ever been won

00:10:17.570 --> 00:10:19.350
have been won at
the proximate level.

00:10:19.350 --> 00:10:20.900
What does proximate means?

00:10:20.900 --> 00:10:24.650
Proximate means you're trying
to understand the how and what

00:10:24.650 --> 00:10:26.060
of a phenomenon.

00:10:26.060 --> 00:10:27.860
How does diabetes work?

00:10:27.860 --> 00:10:30.140
What are some factors
that increase the severity

00:10:30.140 --> 00:10:31.700
of the symptoms of diabetes?

00:10:31.700 --> 00:10:34.040
These questions--
the how and what,

00:10:34.040 --> 00:10:36.350
which is where much of
science operates-- those

00:10:36.350 --> 00:10:38.360
are proximate questions.

00:10:38.360 --> 00:10:40.700
Ultimate questions--
and by the way here,

00:10:40.700 --> 00:10:44.030
people think ultimate means
superior, it's the ultimate.

00:10:44.030 --> 00:10:45.200
That's not what it means.

00:10:45.200 --> 00:10:49.730
Ultimate means the
ultimate Darwinian why.

00:10:49.730 --> 00:10:54.120
Why would the mechanism have
evolved to be of that form?

00:10:54.120 --> 00:10:57.140
So it's not that
ultimate explanations are

00:10:57.140 --> 00:10:59.000
superior to
approximate ones, it's

00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:01.550
that you need both
levels of explanations

00:11:01.550 --> 00:11:04.290
to fully understand
the phenomenon.

00:11:04.290 --> 00:11:09.410
So again, you will only study
these types of explanations

00:11:09.410 --> 00:11:10.994
if you come with an
evolutionary lens.

00:11:10.994 --> 00:11:13.159
Now you might say OK, I'm
not really quite following

00:11:13.159 --> 00:11:13.830
what this is.

00:11:13.830 --> 00:11:15.621
So let me give you a
very concrete example.

00:11:15.621 --> 00:11:18.890
Take, for example,
pregnancy sickness.

00:11:18.890 --> 00:11:21.140
This is a universal
phenomenon that

00:11:21.140 --> 00:11:24.170
happens throughout time
and across cultures.

00:11:24.170 --> 00:11:28.040
Women, at a very predictable
point in their gestation,

00:11:28.040 --> 00:11:29.510
will experience
pregnancy sickness.

00:11:29.510 --> 00:11:32.051
The reason why we call pregnancy
sickness rather than morning

00:11:32.051 --> 00:11:33.620
sickness is because
it doesn't only

00:11:33.620 --> 00:11:36.770
manifest itself in the morning,
although typically, it does.

00:11:36.770 --> 00:11:39.830
So we call it, more
generally, pregnancy sickness.

00:11:39.830 --> 00:11:42.770
Well, what would be
a proximate story

00:11:42.770 --> 00:11:45.890
to tackle when it comes
to pregnancy sickness?

00:11:45.890 --> 00:11:49.880
Well, how do the hormonal
fluctuations of a woman

00:11:49.880 --> 00:11:52.700
affect the severity
of her symptoms?

00:11:52.700 --> 00:11:55.400
That's approximate question.

00:11:55.400 --> 00:12:00.140
The ultimate question is
why have women evolved

00:12:00.140 --> 00:12:02.000
this physiological response?

