01:03:12.580 --> 01:03:16.450
recognition there so it
evokes like a primitive kind

01:03:16.450 --> 01:03:17.410
of response.

01:03:17.410 --> 01:03:20.050
Is there any research
into that or anything

01:03:20.050 --> 01:03:22.122
you've heard about that?

01:03:22.122 --> 01:03:23.830
GAD SAAD: Not sure I
follow the question.

01:03:23.830 --> 01:03:25.119
Can you rephrase it?

01:03:25.119 --> 01:03:26.410
AUDIENCE: Yeah, like a Porsche.

01:03:26.410 --> 01:03:32.200
We know a Porsche is an
expensive, kind of sexy object,

01:03:32.200 --> 01:03:36.490
and having one increases status.

01:03:36.490 --> 01:03:39.940
But, the recognition that
a Porsche is expensive

01:03:39.940 --> 01:03:41.950
and it sounds really
cool and stuff

01:03:41.950 --> 01:03:47.240
like that, that requires a
higher level of processing.

01:03:47.240 --> 01:03:50.650
So how does our biological--

01:03:50.650 --> 01:03:51.550
GAD SAAD: Right.

01:03:51.550 --> 01:03:56.650
So the underlying mechanism is,
of course, not Porsche-related.

01:03:56.650 --> 01:04:00.130
In other words, it's in the
current cultural context

01:04:00.130 --> 01:04:03.660
that status has become
associated with the Porsche

01:04:03.660 --> 01:04:05.470
that that's what we get.

01:04:05.470 --> 01:04:09.100
In other cultures, it might
be the number of cattle heads

01:04:09.100 --> 01:04:10.070
that I own.

01:04:10.070 --> 01:04:14.620
In another culture, it might be
whether I'm a famous painter.

01:04:14.620 --> 01:04:17.560
Picasso was a profoundly
unattractive male

01:04:17.560 --> 01:04:19.510
by any measure.

01:04:19.510 --> 01:04:20.390
He was short.

01:04:20.390 --> 01:04:20.980
He was bald.

01:04:20.980 --> 01:04:21.850
He was overweight.

01:04:21.850 --> 01:04:24.460
He was not particularly
attractive in any way, yet

01:04:24.460 --> 01:04:26.950
he had an extremely
long line up of women

01:04:26.950 --> 01:04:28.840
who were more than
happy to mate with him--

01:04:28.840 --> 01:04:31.420
very beautiful women--
because he was Picasso.

01:04:31.420 --> 01:04:33.490
So the underlying
phenomenon is not

01:04:33.490 --> 01:04:37.680
as though we have genes
for Porsches any more

01:04:37.680 --> 01:04:40.030
than we have genes
for pornography.

01:04:40.030 --> 01:04:44.180
It's that these
modern day products

01:04:44.180 --> 01:04:48.280
tickle evolutionary
principles that exist in us.

01:04:48.280 --> 01:04:49.327
That make sense?

01:04:49.327 --> 01:04:51.160
JORDAN THIBODEAU: Do
the next live question.

01:04:51.160 --> 01:04:51.785
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

01:04:51.785 --> 01:04:55.650
So as an individual
