01:16:40.930 --> 01:16:44.920
Can you talk about the mobility
in friendship issue the US?

01:16:44.920 --> 01:16:47.040
How we're constantly
relocating and whatnot.

01:16:47.040 --> 01:16:49.390
And how can we overcome that?

01:16:49.390 --> 01:16:51.310
GAD SAAD: So that
part I was talking

01:16:51.310 --> 01:16:56.470
about cross-cultural
differences in friendships.

01:16:56.470 --> 01:16:58.510
And one of the arguments
that I've often heard--

01:16:58.510 --> 01:17:01.480
when I was in graduate school,
most of the graduate students

01:17:01.480 --> 01:17:04.390
who were not American, would
always say the same thing--

01:17:04.390 --> 01:17:07.570
you could make friends very
easily with an American,

01:17:07.570 --> 01:17:11.240
but the friendships somehow
seemed to be shallower.

01:17:11.240 --> 01:17:13.570
There are sort of
more ephemeral.

01:17:13.570 --> 01:17:15.310
And so I was thinking,
well, why is that?

01:17:15.310 --> 01:17:16.810
I mean it can't be
because Americans

01:17:16.810 --> 01:17:18.370
are more shallow folks.

01:17:18.370 --> 01:17:19.780
That certainly can't be it.

01:17:19.780 --> 01:17:23.380
And so the argument
that has been proposed

01:17:23.380 --> 01:17:29.470
is that the greater geographic
and socioeconomic mobility

01:17:29.470 --> 01:17:31.360
in the United States--

01:17:31.360 --> 01:17:34.480
today I'm in Atlanta,
tomorrow I'm in Mountain View.

01:17:34.480 --> 01:17:39.380
Today I am a lower
economic status,

01:17:39.380 --> 01:17:42.010
now I'm a dot.com billionaire.

01:17:42.010 --> 01:17:46.060
That mobility causes people
to have a different outlook

01:17:46.060 --> 01:17:49.300
on friendships, whereas when
you come from the old country,

01:17:49.300 --> 01:17:54.790
meaning Lebanon, Italy,
Greece, India, typically

01:17:54.790 --> 01:17:57.220
the place where you're born,
that little village where

01:17:57.220 --> 01:18:00.970
you were born, is where
you're going to typically die.

01:18:00.970 --> 01:18:04.240
And therefore, that's closer
to the evolutionary environment

01:18:04.240 --> 01:18:06.190
in which we've evolved.

01:18:06.190 --> 01:18:09.130
The networks are much tighter.

01:18:09.130 --> 01:18:10.660
They mimic much
more the environment

01:18:10.660 --> 01:18:12.700
in which we evolved,
whereas the environments

01:18:12.700 --> 01:18:14.500
that we see in our
modern environment today

01:18:14.500 --> 01:18:16.660
are not the ones that
we have evolved in.

01:18:16.660 --> 01:18:19.870
That's why in California,
for every single

01:18:19.870 --> 01:18:24.040
of the most banal exchanges,
you have a 600 page

01:18:24.040 --> 01:18:25.870
legal disclaimer form.

01:18:25.870 --> 01:18:27.700
I remember where
we moved from what

01:18:27.700 --> 01:18:29.020
we moved from Montreal to--

01:18:29.020 --> 01:18:31.030
I was a professor at UC Irvine--

01:18:31.030 --> 01:18:36.280
the first place that
we rented, a townhouse,

01:18:36.280 --> 01:18:39.490
the rental agreement
was probably three times

01:18:39.490 --> 01:18:44.180
the size of the Camp David
Accords between Egypt, Lebanon,

01:18:44.180 --> 01:18:45.550
and the United States.

01:18:45.550 --> 01:18:49.150
In 1953, we passed a
certain fumigation,

01:18:49.150 --> 01:18:52.690
you can't sue us if in 17
generations one of your kids

01:18:52.690 --> 01:18:53.920
develops cancer.

01:18:53.920 --> 01:18:56.045
You're reading through
this, you're saying, I mean,

01:18:56.045 --> 01:18:58.600
am I renting an apartment or
is this like a nuclear reactor?

01:18:58.600 --> 01:18:59.920
What's going on?

01:18:59.920 --> 01:19:03.170
Well, the reason
for that is because

01:19:03.170 --> 01:19:06.380
of the anonymity of the current
environment that we live in.

01:19:06.380 --> 01:19:10.940
The social interactions have to
be mandated by these contracts.

01:19:10.940 --> 01:19:15.590
If you're back in Lebanon, well,
I just have to shake your hand

01:19:15.590 --> 01:19:16.680
and that's enough.

01:19:16.680 --> 01:19:19.490
Now that's not because the
Lebanese are more honorable.

01:19:19.490 --> 01:19:21.572
That's because, if
I cheat you once,

01:19:21.572 --> 01:19:23.030
that's the last
time I'm ever going

01:19:23.030 --> 01:19:26.000
to cheat you because I'm going
to be in that environment.

01:19:26.000 --> 01:19:30.500
So you don't need the
7,000-page contract to mandate

01:19:30.500 --> 01:19:31.210
relationships.

01:19:31.210 --> 01:19:33.770
So I argue that
that's what drives

01:19:33.770 --> 01:19:37.940
the cross-cultural differences
and the depth of friendships.

